Text:  The Trout Creek Mountains are semi @-@ arid because they are in the eastern rain shadow of mountain ranges to the west . Much of the annual precipitation occurs between the beginning of March and the end of June . Most of the rest falls as snow during the fall and winter months .   at elevations below 6 @,@ 000 feet ( 1 @,@ 800 m ) usually melts by April ; however , at the higher elevations , snow can remain until mid @-@ June .
